When we look through the scriptures,

00:36:38.170 --> 00:36:41.170
we see many examples, but for the next few minutes,

00:36:41.170 --> 00:36:43.769
we're going to think about Barnabas.

00:36:44.690 --> 00:36:49.690
And how Barnabas was able to share what he learned with Paul.

00:36:50.650 --> 00:36:52.889
And as we think about what happened

00:36:52.889 --> 00:36:56.449
in that interaction between Barnabas and Paul,

00:36:56.449 --> 00:36:59.409
we're going to learn five lessons.

00:36:59.409 --> 00:37:03.369
Five lessons that teach us how to handle training

00:37:03.369 --> 00:37:05.690
others and passing on what we've learned.

00:37:06.570 --> 00:37:08.690
So the first lesson, if you turn with me,

00:37:08.690 --> 00:37:12.530
please, through the book of Acts, Acts chapter nine.

00:37:13.489 --> 00:37:17.610
This takes us to the year around the year 36C.

00:37:17.610 --> 00:37:22.610
So Saul has already become a Christian now after a while

00:37:22.769 --> 00:37:24.409
he arrives in Jerusalem.

00:37:24.409 --> 00:37:26.210
So what happens?

00:37:26.210 --> 00:37:28.769
In verse 26 of chapter nine, it says,

00:37:28.769 --> 00:37:32.250
on arriving in Jerusalem, he, that's Paul,

00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:35.289
made efforts to join the disciples.

00:37:35.289 --> 00:37:37.050
But they were all afraid of him.

00:37:37.050 --> 00:37:38.050
I wonder why?

00:37:39.369 --> 00:37:42.449
Because they did not believe he was a disciple.

00:37:42.449 --> 00:37:46.369
They were thinking this is going to be a very dangerous thing.

00:37:47.250 --> 00:37:50.329
But now what happened in verse 27?

00:37:50.329 --> 00:37:55.329
So Barnabas came to his aid and led him to the apostles.

00:37:56.570 --> 00:37:59.650
So we see as pictured here,

00:37:59.650 --> 00:38:04.690
Barnabas saw the potential in Saul

00:38:04.690 --> 00:38:07.690
and believed that really he could be useful

00:38:07.690 --> 00:38:09.050
in Jehovah's service.

00:38:09.050 --> 00:38:12.250
So he risked his reputation, you might say,

00:38:12.250 --> 00:38:15.329
by supporting or sponsoring Saul

00:38:15.329 --> 00:38:18.050
and taking him to the apostles.

00:38:18.969 --> 00:38:22.409
So what's the lesson that we learn from this?

00:38:22.409 --> 00:38:26.250
Try to see the potential in others.

00:38:27.130 --> 00:38:30.730
And don't worry about if you perhaps encourage them

00:38:30.730 --> 00:38:34.090
and you give them support, you sponsor them, you might say,

00:38:34.090 --> 00:38:36.210
and then they don't really turn out well

00:38:36.210 --> 00:38:38.250
that now all of a sudden your reputation

00:38:38.250 --> 00:38:40.010
is going to be tarnished.

00:38:40.010 --> 00:38:42.570
Remember, it's not all about you.

00:38:42.570 --> 00:38:45.329
It's what is good for the work.

00:38:45.329 --> 00:38:46.769
So that's the first lesson.

00:38:46.769 --> 00:38:50.289
Try to see the potential in others.

00:38:50.329 --> 00:38:53.210
Now if we turn across to Acts chapter 11,

00:38:54.369 --> 00:38:59.369
this goes about nine years later, around the year 45 CE.

