Now in chapter 11 of Acts,

00:39:03.409 --> 00:39:06.690
the work is going ahead in the Gentile field

00:39:06.690 --> 00:39:10.090
and particularly in the city of Antioch.

00:39:10.090 --> 00:39:14.050
So Barnabas was assigned by the brothers

00:39:14.050 --> 00:39:18.170
to go and help the congregation in Antioch.

00:39:18.170 --> 00:39:21.570
Well, let's look down verses 25 and 26

00:39:21.570 --> 00:39:24.050
because as soon as Barnabas arrived there,

00:39:24.050 --> 00:39:28.010
he realized he needed help.

00:39:28.010 --> 00:39:30.010
So what did he do?

00:39:30.010 --> 00:39:32.570
Well, in verse 25 it says,

00:39:32.570 --> 00:39:35.610
he that's Barnabas went to Tassus

00:39:35.610 --> 00:39:38.849
to make a thorough search for Saul.

00:39:40.130 --> 00:39:42.489
So he went to find Saul.

00:39:42.489 --> 00:39:46.050
He remembered this is a man who could speak Greek

00:39:46.170 --> 00:39:48.409
and was well educated.

00:39:48.409 --> 00:39:51.769
He'd be able to help him with the Gentile field.

00:39:51.769 --> 00:39:54.449
It's interesting that when you look at a map,

00:39:54.449 --> 00:39:59.449
you'll notice that it's about 120 miles from Antioch to Tassus

00:40:00.969 --> 00:40:03.050
or about 200 kilometers.

00:40:04.010 --> 00:40:05.650
It mentions here in verse 25,

00:40:05.650 --> 00:40:07.409
he made a thorough search for Saul.

00:40:07.409 --> 00:40:08.409
Why?

00:40:08.409 --> 00:40:10.730
Well, if we compare first Corinthians

00:40:10.730 --> 00:40:14.530
where Paul lists all the things he did, many of those,

00:40:14.530 --> 00:40:18.289
it appears happened in those nine years.

00:40:18.289 --> 00:40:20.090
He was shipwrecked several times,

00:40:20.090 --> 00:40:21.610
put it into prison and so on.

00:40:21.610 --> 00:40:23.769
So he was very busy.

00:40:23.769 --> 00:40:25.849
Barnabas sought him out.

00:40:25.849 --> 00:40:27.130
And then what did he have to do?

00:40:27.130 --> 00:40:30.969
Well, in verse 26 it says after he found him,

00:40:30.969 --> 00:40:33.489
he brought him to Antioch.

00:40:33.489 --> 00:40:34.690
So what did he have to do?

00:40:34.690 --> 00:40:37.369
He had to convince Saul.

00:40:37.369 --> 00:40:39.530
You could imagine that might have been a little difficult

00:40:39.530 --> 00:40:42.690
because Saul was having productive ministry.

00:40:42.690 --> 00:40:44.969
So he brought him to Antioch.

00:40:44.969 --> 00:40:46.809
Then verse 26 says,

00:40:46.809 --> 00:40:50.769
for a whole year they assembled with them in the congregation

00:40:50.769 --> 00:40:53.449
and taught quite a crowd.

00:40:53.449 --> 00:40:56.449
So Barnabas didn't take Paul and say,

00:40:56.449 --> 00:40:58.090
now I'm going to teach you.

00:40:58.090 --> 00:41:00.849
He just had him work along with him.

00:41:00.849 --> 00:41:02.650
And as they work together,

00:41:02.650 --> 00:41:05.170
that would have given Saul some training.

00:41:06.369 --> 00:41:09.610
So what's the lesson that we learned?

00:41:09.610 --> 00:41:11.409
Be willing to make the effort.

00:41:11.409 --> 00:41:15.130
You see, Barnabas not only saw the potential,

00:41:15.130 --> 00:41:18.170
but he was willing to go and find Saul,

00:41:18.170 --> 00:41:20.489
then convince him to come and work with him.

00:41:20.489 --> 00:41:22.369
And then they worked together.

00:41:22.369 --> 00:41:24.489
So that's the second lesson.

00:41:24.489 --> 00:41:27.769
The third lesson is in Acts 13.

00:41:28.730 --> 00:41:33.730
So after Barnabas and Saul were in Antioch for some time,

00:41:33.730 --> 00:41:36.650
what happened in verse two?

00:41:36.650 --> 00:41:38.889
It says as they were ministering to Jehovah

00:41:38.889 --> 00:41:42.329
and fasting, the Holy Spirit said,

00:41:42.329 --> 00:41:45.849
set aside for me Barnabas and Saul

00:41:45.849 --> 00:41:48.010
for the work to which I have called them.

00:41:49.010 --> 00:41:51.570
Well now this is the time when they're going out

00:41:51.570 --> 00:41:53.449
in their missionary field.

00:41:54.409 --> 00:41:58.769
But notice the Holy Spirit mentions Barnabas and Saul.

00:41:58.769 --> 00:42:01.849
So in this illustration we see who's taking the lead.

00:42:01.849 --> 00:42:05.449
Barnabas, Saul's following along.

00:42:05.449 --> 00:42:07.969
But if we look down further in verse 13

00:42:07.969 --> 00:42:12.050
of the same chapter, we see there's a little change.

00:42:12.050 --> 00:42:15.889
Saul starts to use a name that is more common in that area.

00:42:15.889 --> 00:42:17.929
Paul, but what does it say?

00:42:17.929 --> 00:42:21.730
Now Paul and his companions would have to see.

00:42:21.730 --> 00:42:26.010
And from here on, it seems that Paul took the lead.

00:42:27.369 --> 00:42:29.690
Now let's just imagine for a little bit

00:42:29.690 --> 00:42:31.130
that you were Barnabas.

00:42:31.130 --> 00:42:33.530
Maybe we could imagine ourselves saying

00:42:33.570 --> 00:42:35.690
quietly to Saul or Paul,

00:42:35.690 --> 00:42:37.929
whatever he was calling himself at that time.

